<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1580,2002]" pageId="6" pageNumber="515">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,349,1724,1750]" pageId="6" pageNumber="515">Recognition.</emphasis>
This species is recognized by its cruciate parameres. The lateral, cross-like projections on the paramere are located at mid-length, concealed by the gonocoxal plate (in ventral view) and are much longer than those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Edwards" authorityYear="1930" box="[248,377,1796,1822]" class="Insecta" family="Thaumaleidae" genus="Austrothaumalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="515" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chilensis">
<emphasis box="[248,377,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="515">A. chilensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
